The paper discusses the use of superconducting circuits for building an accelerator for SHA-256 engines used in Bitcoin mining applications. This falls under the category of computer architecture (cs.AR) and emerging technologies (cs.ET). The paper also discusses the challenges faced by superconducting technology, such as limited device density and new failure modes, which are relevant to the categories of digital circuits (cs.DC), electromagnetics (cs.EM), and software engineering (cs.SE).
